    <note>Tan(3) Zhimo [1586] His grandfather Zhang's [3816] (q.v.) fourth generation ancestor moved from Hengzhou, Hengyang xian to Tanzhou, Changsha xian. Zhang was a private scholar who did not seek office, but gained some fame as a teacher. Zhimo's wife, Gong(2) Shi, was also from a classicist family (rujia). Zhimo's brother, Zhigu [3817], received his university degree (shangshe) in 1127 and had a modest career before he died in 1143. Zhang Kuo, WJ, 9.18a; Hu Yin, WJ, 26.20b; Wang Zao, WJ, 28.5b. CBD, 5, 4262.</note>
